ally important thinker shows why the issues Merleau-Ponty raised are, more than ever, those of our time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aPhenomenologyxHistory. 0aPhilosophy, Frenchy20th century. 0aPhilosophy, Modern. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh  aaesthetics.  aembodiment.  alanguage.  amedium.  aontology.  aperception.  aphenomenology.1 aBarbaras, Renaud, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarbaras, Renaud.1 aTodd, Jane Marie.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311072901640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823275700zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823275700423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780823275700.jpg  a978-3-11-072901-6  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK